                <li>
            <span class="who">
                <span class="">Julian Weinberg</span>:
            </span>
            <span class="utterance" who="#weinbergJ" start="1530.706" end="x">. . . We remained in the <a class="placename" href="#vothC65" type="camp">Ghetto</a> for more than five years. Of these old pieces of clothing, of these old shoes which came back torn, because they were searching for various valuable . . . valuable objects [hidden] in the clothes; so the clothes were torn up, altered. The shoes as well. In our <a class="placename" href="#vothC65" type="camp">Ghetto</a> the better things were repaired, and then partly distributed among the remaining population in the Ghetto, and partly it was also shipped out by the Germans for the bombed-out German population. [Pause]</span>
        </li>
