            </span>
            <span class="utterance" who="#weinbergJ" start="1965.065" end="x">Yes. We were housed directly in these two buildings—which have become some kind of <a class="term" href="#vothG_lager">lager</a>, and from this instant we were regarded as a <a class="term" href="#vothG_lager">lager</a>, like in <a class="placename" href="#vothC4" type="camp">Auschwitz</a>, <a class="placename" href="#vothC25" type="camp">Dachau</a> or the kind. We were subject to all disciplinary . . .</span>
